Windows 10 ARM64 Optimized for Lumia 950/XL



Thanks to Fadil Fadz for making an Installation Video! I am aware some users have viewing issues on this page

UPDATE: I am struggling to find decent time to work on Version 3, it is coming, but not for a few months! For now Version 2 will Reboot ever 2 hours (Expired Insider Trial), so use Version 1 for now

Those of you that aren't aware, Lumia 950/XL users can install full Windows 10 onto their devices thanks to the magic from the devs at WoA-Project (https://github.com/WOA-Project)
But as expected it can sometime run slow and become a burden due to the various tasks and activities running in the background.

I started making this as a means to have a slightly more fluid experience when running Windows 10 ARM64, attempting to remove Services that aren't required or needed, Built-In Apps and stuff like that.

I do not condone Piracy, If used in any other way than with WoA launcher then you will need to purchase an Activation Key!

This has only been tested by me and possibly a couple other people. I am in need of Testers and people that can contribute to the Project. There WILL be instabilities and issues as everybody uses Windows differently, I cannot replicate every scenario.

Install Guide

Easy to install!
Jump to Sections: Mass Storage Mode, Deploying the Image to device, Post-installation.

Step 1:
Put device into 'Mass Storage Mode'

This step is intended for Users who have NOT got the 'Developer Menu' installed from WoA-Deployer or have NOT entered Mass Storage Mode

NOTE: If it is the FIRST TIME you are booting to Mass Storage Mode, WPInternals will have to 'enable' it first, don't panic it has to flash a few files it's normal, just follow the onscreen instructions.. The device will reboot several times.. if you have any issues restore back to Windows Mobile with Windows Device Recovery Tool from 'Flash Mode'

**WARNING FOR NEW USERS**
If you have worries BACKUP your device with Win32DiskImager while in Mass Storage Mode.
DON'T modify any Partitions on the device with Windows yourself. Several Partitions are NEEDED to make your phone work, without them you WILL loose capabilities. Examples are DPP and ESPEFI (The rest are hidden but still don't mess with them), Software used in this guide has been designed by the Devs to modify what is needed without user mess ups.

Open WPInternals, Interupt Boot.

Turn OFF the device and leave it UNPLUGGED.

Open up WPInternals, and click on 'Manual Mode', then 'Interrupt the Boot Process'
 


Now plug in your device. it should appear like this.

Click 'Manual Mode' again.


Now Click 'Switch to Mass Storage Mode' the device will go into Mass Storage Mode.


Step 2:
Deploy Image with WoA Deployer
(Phone should still be plugged in and in Mass Storage Mode ready and waiting)

If you require, go to the Advanced tab and have a look at the settings, I usually select 'Use Compact Deployment' as it gives more free space after installation. Also consider keeping Windows 10 Mobile, and allocation 20GB to Windows ARM because after Windows ARM is installed and set up, you can enable Dual-Boot from WoA Deployer!
I also untick 'Clean 'Downloaded'...' because I am on a previous set of Drivers which work better for me but this option is usually best left default for first time install.

Open WoA Deployer and Make it use the Modified Image

For reasons beyond me at the moment, WoA Deployer doesn't load my WIM it throws an 'Invalid WIM File' error.
So we have to first load the Untouched WIM file:

You should have my Version2.wim and the ISO install.wim in the same folder together. Load WoA Deployer and click 'Browse':


Now we have to rename the WIM files. Rename 'install.wim' to anything you want like 'original' or something.



If you did it correct it should now start Deploying to your device! It will take a while, go have a nice cuppa tea.



NOTE: You WILL recieve an 'Invalid WIM File' error as soon as it finishes injecting Drivers, this is expected so DON'T PANIC, just press OK and eject your Device safely, Reboot and let it finish Setup

Post-install

This section is for when you are finally on the Windows Desktop!

Scripts :
(All scripts used can be found in the GitHub Repo found down the page)

I have added a SetupComplete.cmd script in 'C:\Windows\Setup' of the Image, this disables some Telemetry, Cortana, Update and a few other things with the Registry. it also removes some Windows Updates that are known to cause issues.

'newuser.bat' is located in 'C:\' and it is a 'RunOnce' script that loads when a NEW user account is made and logged in, this is executed after first install, because you set up your user account. Expect a bunch of Command Prompt windows to open and close shortly after loading the desktop because it further disables some features that are stored in the Current Users Registry Key, it also will disable a list of 'Unneeded' Services, most of these will say not installed because I removed alot with WinReducer, it is more of a 'make sure' measure. It also adds the 'GodMode' folder on the Desktop which is just the 'Administrators' Control Panel. It shows with no name.

Optional:

I have also added a couple Scripts onto the Desktop that are up to you what you do with..
The first is an 'Update Switch' script that just turns On or Off Windows Update Services. Purpose of this is to Disable Update Services when NOT using the Microsoft Store, and Enable Update Services when you NEED to use the Store (Microsoft Store requires Update Services to work)
It can also disable a bunch of Services not needed (Same list as found in 'newuser.bat').

The second is my Windows 10 Toolbox to change various parts of Windows. (See Page header link for more info on what it does)

Recommended Actions to help Performance
(Very brief no screenshots)

Disable special effects.

These include Windows Shadows, Window Contents when Dragging etc.

Open touch keyboard, hold Win + R  and type sysdm.cpl
then goto the 'Advanced' tab, In the 'Performance' box press 'Settings', Click 'Adjust for best performance'
(I usually re-tick 'Smooth edges of screen fonts' to keep nicer text)

Install an Adblock for Edge and try to visit Mobile/Tablet versions of sites.
For example: touch.facebook.com works really well with Edge

Keyboard:

The predictive text etc causes lag when using the touch keyboard. 
Press the Settings icon in the top left of the Keyboard, Tap the bottop Cog icon, Turn off everything EXCEPT 'Show the touch keyboard when not in tablet mode and there's no physical keyboard attached' (this option will prevent the keyboard showing)

Issues:

There will be the usual issues that a standard install with WoA Deployer, this device was not designed to run a Full Desktop Experience.. So Expect the odd random reboot, sometimes the device will get really hot, look at woaproject.net forum for info on what issues are present.
